Lutz, Respondent, v. Lutz, Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. January 10, 1890.)

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Brady and Daniels, JJ.

A. B. Clark, for appellant. Ernest Hall, for respondent.

No opinion. Motion denied, upon appellant’s stipulating to argue at February term and paying $10, costs of this motion.
